WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 767
Chapter 767
(House Bill 1430)
AN ACT concerning
Maryland Public Charter School Program – School Facilities – Funding
FOR the purpose of requiring the Interagency Commission on School Construction to
distribute certain funds to public charter schools for the maintenance and operation
of capital improvements to public charter school facilities, debt service, or rent or lease
payments; requiring certain public charter schools to report to the Interagency
Commission on School Construction on the status of certain projects; and generally
relating to the funding of public charter school facilities in the Maryland Public
Charter School Program.
BY adding to
Article – Education
Section 9–109(c)
Annotated Code of Maryland
(2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
Article – Education
9–109.
(C) (1) (I) IN THIS SUBSECTION,, “PUBLIC THE FOLLOWING WORDS
HAVE THE MEANINGS INDICATED.
(II) “PUBLIC “PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL FACILITIES” MEANS
PREMISES THAT ARE:
(I) 1. (I) OWNED OR LEASED BY A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL;
OR
(II) 2. (II) OCCUPIED AND UTILIZED BY A PUBLIC CHARTER
SCHOOL TO PROVIDE A PROGRAM OF PRIMARY OR SECONDARY EDUCATION TO ITS
STUDENTS.
(III) “TOTAL AGGREGATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT” DOES NOT
INCLUDE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEMS THAT:
– 1 –

Ch. 767 2026 LAWS OF MARYLAND
1. HAVE CLOSED OVER 50 SCHOOLS SINCE 2010; AND
2. MADE SURPLUS FACILITIES AVAILABLE TO CHARTER
SCHOOLS.
(2) (I) 1. THE SUBJECT TO SUBSUBPARAGRAPH 2 OF THIS
SUBPARAGRAPH, THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION
SHALL DISTRIBUTE FUNDS TO PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOLS FOR THE MAINTENANCE
AND OPERATION OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SUBSECTION FOR CAPITAL
IMPROVEMENTS TO PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL FACILITIES, DEBT SERVICE, OR RENT
OR LEASE PAYMENTS.
2. A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL MAY RECEIVE FUNDS
UNDER THIS SUBSECTION ONLY IF THE OPERATOR’S MOST RECENT REQUIRED
CERTIFIED FINANCIAL AUDIT IS UNQUALIFIED.
(II) FUNDS DISBURSED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS
PARAGRAPH SHALL BE PAID DIRECTLY TO THE PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL AND MAY
NOT BE PAID TO A LOCAL GOVERNING BODY OR COUNTY BOARD.
(3) IF A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL IS LOCATED IN A BUILDING OWNED
BY THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM, THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL
CONSTRUCTION MAY NOT DISTRIBUTE FUNDS TO THE PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL
FOR CAPITAL IMPROVEMENTS TO THE SCHOOL FACILITY, DEBT SERVICE, OR RENT
OR LEASE PAYMENTS UNDER THIS SUBSECTION IN FISCAL YEARS DURING WHICH THE
SCHOOL FACILITY IS UNDERGOING A PROJECT THAT IS RECEIVING STATE FUNDING
THROUGH THE CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT PROGRAM.
(4) IF THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF THE CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT PROGRAM
IN A FISCAL YEAR IS LESS THAN THE TOTAL AMOUNT IN THE PRIOR FISCAL YEAR, THE
AMOUNT OF FUNDS DISTRIBUTED TO PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOLS UNDER THIS
SUBSECTION FOR THE FISCAL YEAR SHALL BE PROPORTIONATELY REDUCED.
(5) THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION
MAY NOT USE FUNDS DISTRIBUTED TO A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL UNDER THIS
SUBSECTION AS JUSTIFICATION TO REDUCE THE AMOUNT PROVIDED TO A LOCAL
SCHOOL SYSTEM THROUGH THE CAPITAL IMPROVEMENT PROGRAM.
(6) A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL THAT RECEIVES FUNDS UNDER THIS
SUBSECTION DURING A FISCAL YEAR SHALL REPORT TO THE INTERAGENCY
COMMISSION ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION ON THE STATUS OF ANY PROJECT FOR
CAPITAL IMPROVEMENTS TO PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL FACILITIES, DEBT SERVICE,
– 2 –

WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 767
OR RENT OR LEASE PAYMENTS BEFORE THE PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL MAY RECEIVE
FUNDS FOR THE FOLLOWING FISCAL YEAR.
(3) (7) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2028 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR
THEREAFTER, THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN
APPROPRIATION FOR THE MAINTENANCE AND OPERATION OF CAPITAL
IMPROVEMENTS TO PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL FACILITIES, DEBT SERVICE, OR RENT
OR LEASE PAYMENTS THAT IS EQUAL TO THE TOTAL AGGREGATE STUDENT
ENROLLMENT IN THE MARYLAND PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL PROGRAM FOR THE
PRIOR FISCAL YEAR MULTIPLIED BY $1,600 $200.
(4) (8) (I) THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL
CONSTRUCTION SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS SUBSECTION.
(II) IN THE REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I)
OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION
SHALL INCLUDE REGULATIONS THAT:
1. ESTABLISH THE PROCEDURES TO COMPLY WITH
PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION IF A LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SUBMITS A
MID–YEAR CAPITAL PROJECT FUNDING REQUEST; AND
2. ENSURE A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL RECEIVES
FUNDS UNDER THIS SUBSECTION IF THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM RESCINDS A
CAPITAL PROJECT FUNDING REQUEST AND THE PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL IS
SUBSEQUENTLY ELIGIBLE FOR FUNDING UNDER THIS SUBSECTION.
SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
1, 2026.
Approved by the Governor, May 26, 2026.
– 3 –

